Class PlayerProfile

java.lang.Object
fr.connexe.ui.game.PlayerProfile
public class PlayerProfile extends Object
Contains all data for a player who's about to play a game: input settings and appearance.

  • Property Details

    • controllerDetected

      public BooleanProperty controllerDetectedProperty

      Returns the property that indicates whether a controller is detected for the player. This property can be used to listen for changes in the controller detection status.

      This is only used by the JavaFX UI, so it doesn't really matter for the GameSession. A cleaner approach would be to separate the UI-state from the raw data, but this would be way too complex for something so dumb.

      Is false for keyboard inputs.

      See Also:
      • isControllerDetected()
      • setControllerDetected(boolean)
      • controllerDetectedProperty()
